{
  "stem": "13313.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she says, well, I have these Jewish kids here with me, and I want them to be baptized.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he says, where are their parents?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, their parents-- father's been deported, and the mother I don't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Oh, he says, I'm very sorry, but I won't baptize these children without the permission of their parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Quite interesting.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So as a result of his position, we were not baptized at the time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't take it beyond that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did they take you to Catholic church?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to mass.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were-- we were-- we were forced, literally forced, in spite of anything, to-- to-- to behave as good Christians.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were taught the Christian prayers, the Hail Mary and the other prayers, and we went to mass every Sunday to-- to the other small village of [INAUDIBLE], not too far away, and went to church on a regular basis.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we prayed the Christian prayers before and after meals.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were very Catholic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I didn't mind going to that church because that church had some kind of a-- of a grotto, a little altar to some miraculous-- miracle-performing saint, and there was a little fountain there with-- with-- with water, and since we were really deprived of food and drink, it was an opportunity to quench our thirst, so that was a good side of going to church.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Well, it turned out that the Mrs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Roggeman, not so much Mr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Roggeman, turned out to be a very vicious anti-Semitic and very sadistic person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she turned our experience into a real hell.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And anything, it was a-- we were there for over two years, they were two years of starvation, hard work, and beatings, on nonstop basis.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
